---
import Heading from "../components/ui/Heading.astro"
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro"
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Learn more about Yash Agarwal — software engineer, tinkerer, and writer."
>
  <Heading level="h2" as="h1" class="mt-6 mb-6">About</Heading>

  <div class="space-y-6">
    <p>
      I'm Yash — a computer nerd by heart and software engineer by profession.
      I grew up tinkering with computers, breaking things, and putting them back
      together. That curiosity never left. Today, I'm a Staff Software Engineer
      at <a href="https://netskope.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Netskope</a>,
      building CASB security products that protect business data at rest.
    </p>

    <p>
      My professional journey has been shaped by a series of deliberate choices.
      After deciding <a href="/notes/2022-01-26-why-i-decided-to-not-join-isro">not to join ISRO</a>,
      I spent over three years at Cisco Systems working on intrusion detection
      and cloud-native security monitoring. I joined Netskope in 2022 and have
      been there since, working across the CASB API product line — migrating
      customers, improving performance, and eventually leading technical initiatives
      as a Staff Engineer.
    </p>

    <p>
      Outside of work, I'm building <a href="https://mumsmemories.app" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Mum's Memories</a> —
      a minimal baby journaling app. It's a side project that combines my love
      for building useful things with a personal need. I write about it, and
      everything else I'm learning, on this site.
    </p>

    <Heading level="h3" as="h2" class="mt-8 mb-4">What this site is about</Heading>

    <p>
      This site is my public brain dump. I write about software engineering,
      infrastructure, security, and occasionally life. No agenda, no SEO
      optimization, no newsletter-first strategy. Just notes and thoughts
      that I want to share with the world.
    </p>

    <p>
      I write for myself first — to clarify my thinking. If you find something
      useful here, that's a bonus. You can browse all notes on the
      <a href="/notes">notes page</a> or filter by <a href="/tags">tags</a> and
      <a href="/categories">categories</a>.
    </p>

    <Heading level="h3" as="h2" class="mt-8 mb-4">Contact</Heading>

    <p>
      If you want to reach out, the best way is on
      <a href="https://twitter.com/yashagarwal" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Twitter</a> or
      <a href="https://github.com/yashhere" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>.
      I'm also on <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/theyashagarwal" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn</a>.
    </p>

    <p>
      For longer conversations, subscribe to my
      <a href="/newsletter">newsletter</a> — I send occasional updates about
      what I'm building and thinking about.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
